{"id":1539,"date":"2024-11-15T10:49:31","date_gmt":"2024-11-15T15:49:31","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/localdev\/viking\/2022\/01\/24\/article-title-can-be-on-two-lines-6\/"},"modified":"2024-11-20T09:36:16","modified_gmt":"2024-11-20T14:36:16","slug":"dan-clark-technical-sales-reps-2013-grey-cup-winner","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/vikingfire.ca\/dan-clark-technical-sales-reps-2013-grey-cup-winner\/","title":{"rendered":"From All-Star CFL Athlete to Dedicated Fire Alarm Sales Rep"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>At Viking Fire Protection, we believe in showcasing our dedicated workforce. We are proud to be the employer of choice for the industry\u2019s most experienced and talented fire protection professionals. Because we value our exceptional specialists, across Canada, we dedicate a segment of our blog, the \u201cJoin the Fire Protection Best!\u201d series, to share their unique stories.<\/p>\n<div>\n<div class=\"ivm-image-view-model pvs-entity__image \">\n<p>For this article, we have chosen to highlight a Technical Sales Representative at our Viking Regina branch: Dan Clark. This story is about an exceptional athlete whose journey from the world of professional football to fire alarm sales has been nothing short of impressive.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<h2>A Veteran Offensive Lineman joins the Viking Fire Alarm Sales Team<\/h2>\n<p>In the Viking Regina office, one of our technical sales reps actually won the 2013 Grey Cup title: his name is Dan R. Clark. Dan&#8217;s transition from a career in professional football, as an offensive lineman for the Saskatchewan Roughriders, to<a href=\"https:\/\/vikingfire.ca\/solutions\/fire-alarm\/\"> fire alarm<\/a> sales has been truly remarkable.<\/p>\n<p>When Dan joined the Regina team, he dove headfirst into his role, setting an ambitious goal for himself: to become \u201cthe best fire alarm salesperson in the province.\u201d His unwavering dedication, along with his enthusiastic team spirit, has already set him on that path. Dan\u2019s quick success stems from his relentless drive, commitment to learning, and the outstanding attitude he brings to every task. Winning the Grey Cup and making his first touchdown are among his best memories in playing professional football, having already achieved these memorable milestones, he\u2019s now striving for new heights in his sales career.<\/p>\n<p>&#8220;When Dan came on board, we had almost no requests for fire alarm pricing. But Dan immediately hit the streets, reaching out to every potential client he could. His outgoing personality and strong customer service commitment have already yielded results, with new pricing requests coming in daily. Dan has built genuine relationships with electrical contractors and suppliers in our area, leading to a steady increase in his sales numbers. Remarkably, he even helped us secure several large-scale projects\u2014an impressive feat for anyone, let alone someone so new to the field.&#8221;-Mike Monette, District Manager<\/p>\n<p>In his past football life, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.riderville.com\/tag\/dan-clark\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Dan Clark<\/a> played with the Riders from 2009 to 2022. He was CFL all-star, <span class=\"s1\">named the Roughriders Most Outstanding Lineman, <\/span>and shared in the Riders\u2019 45-23 victory over the Hamilton Tiger-Cats in the 2013 Grey Cup game at old Mosaic Stadium.<\/p>\n<p><em>In the picture below, Dan Clark #67, when the Saskatchewan Roughriders took on the Ottawa Red Blacks in CFL in Regina, SK on Saturday, August 24th, 2019. Photo Credit: Electric Umbrella\/Liam Richards<\/em><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-9454 size-full\" title=\"Viking technical sales reps won the 2013 Grey Cup: Dan Clark\" src=\"https:\/\/vikingfire.ca\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/blog-and-featured-images-viking-8.png\" alt=\"Viking technical sales reps won the 2013 Grey Cup: Dan Clark\" width=\"1200\" height=\"780\" srcset=\"https:\/\/vikingfire.ca\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/blog-and-featured-images-viking-8.png 1200w, https:\/\/vikingfire.ca\/wp-content\/smush-webp\/2022\/01\/blog-and-featured-images-viking-8-300x195.png.webp 300w, https:\/\/vikingfire.ca\/wp-content\/smush-webp\/2022\/01\/blog-and-featured-images-viking-8-1024x666.png.webp 1024w, https:\/\/vikingfire.ca\/wp-content\/smush-webp\/2022\/01\/blog-and-featured-images-viking-8-768x499.png.webp 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/><\/p>\n<h2>Growing Expertise in Fire Alarm Systems<\/h2>\n<p>Dan\u2019s path to becoming a leading fire alarm salesperson is built on the strong foundation of his 13+ year sports career. Transitioning from professional athlete to an industry specialist, Dan has demonstrated an incredible ability to learn, adapt and grow. His knowledge expands daily through self-study and support from his Viking Fire team, especially his colleagues in British Columbia and Alberta. In particular Bob Kerr, Mike McIntyre, and Paul Huntington who provided mentorship and support to help Dan develop his expertise.<\/p>\n<h3>&#8220;My favorite part of the job is knowing that I\u2019m helping to keep people safe. It\u2019s incredibly rewarding to provide solutions that protect lives and property. Plus, I enjoy meeting new people and building relationships with clients.&#8221;-Dan R. Clark, Technical Sales Rep.<\/h3>\n<p>Which achievement is Dan most proud of so far at Viking Fire? He answered with the following: &#8220;I\u2019m most proud of how quickly I adapted to the fire alarm industry despite having no prior background. Learning the technical aspects and regulations has been challenging, but I embraced the challenge. It\u2019s been a steep learning curve, but having the support and guidance of my colleagues has made a significant impact. Their expertise and encouragement have been invaluable in guiding my career with Viking Fire&#8221;.<\/p>\n<p>According to his district manager, Dan\u2019s eager-to-learn attitude, coupled with his commitment to excellence, makes him an ideal student. His determination to stay on top of industry trends and product knowledge is apparent in every client interaction, ensuring Viking Fire clients receive the most informed service possible.<\/p>\n<p><em>Photo Credit: Riderville.com &#8211; Dan Clark Named 2022 Jake Gaudaur Veterans&#8217; Award Winner<\/em><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-9452 size-full\" title=\"Viking technical sales reps won the 2013 Grey Cup: Dan Clark\" src=\"https:\/\/vikingfire.ca\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/blog-and-featured-images-viking-9.png\" alt=\"Viking technical sales reps won the 2013 Grey Cup: Dan Clark\" width=\"1200\" height=\"780\" srcset=\"https:\/\/vikingfire.ca\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/blog-and-featured-images-viking-9.png 1200w, https:\/\/vikingfire.ca\/wp-content\/smush-webp\/2022\/01\/blog-and-featured-images-viking-9-300x195.png.webp 300w, https:\/\/vikingfire.ca\/wp-content\/smush-webp\/2022\/01\/blog-and-featured-images-viking-9-1024x666.png.webp 1024w, https:\/\/vikingfire.ca\/wp-content\/smush-webp\/2022\/01\/blog-and-featured-images-viking-9-768x499.png.webp 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/><\/p>\n<h2>A Lasting Impact on Team Culture<\/h2>\n<p>Since he started working at Viking Regina, Dan&#8217;s energy and work ethic have had a lasting impact on his office&#8217;s culture: &#8220;Dan\u2019s biggest contributions to our team are his amazing team-first attitude and strong work ethic. There is no task Dan will say no to. His priority has always been to do what is best for the group. He helps foster a supportive, collaborative, and positive environment in our office. It\u2019s a pleasure working with Dan every day.&#8221; &#8211; Mike Monette, District Manager<\/p>\n<p>Clark\u2019s contributions have not been limited to the field. He was among the most active players in the community and has embraced his role as an ambassador.\u00a0 In fact, he was the 2022 Jake Gaudaur Veterans\u2019 Award Winner: this recognition is awarded to a Canadian player who demonstrates the attributes of Canada\u2019s veterans: Strength, perseverance, courage, comradeship and contribution to Canadian communities. At the awards ceremony, the CFL Commissioner, Randy Ambrosie, commented the following about Dan: \u201cHe stands tall in the Riders locker room as a veteran and as a leader, and every bit as important is what he stands for in the community. He is an incredible role model to his teammates, the entire league and all Canadians.\u201d<\/p>\n<p><em>The following Rider Radio video is one of Dan&#8217;s latest interviews where he discusses his CFL retirement and mentions his new fire alarm sales career:<\/em><\/p>\n<p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"RIDER RADIO: Longtime Riders&#039; OL Dan Clark explains how he came to grips with CFL retirement\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/lNxJWta3e8k?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"HMZyUxfpaKOqYknGYzBkgbOfYbcgWdYsLo full-width t-14 t-normal t-black display-flex align-items-center\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Attracting the Best Talent in the Industry<\/h3>\n<p>Dan&#8217;s journey from professional sports to technical sales continues to inspire us all, and we have no doubt he\u2019ll achieve his goal of becoming the best in the province. Here\u2019s to Dan\u2014a rising star in the fire alarm industry and a cherished member of our team!<\/p>\n<p>At Viking, we take pride in employing the best technical sales representatives in the industry. We value and reward our outstanding specialists, reflecting a high employee retention rate. By choosing a career as a technical sales rep. at Viking, you gain access to mentorship and solid professional guidance from our staff. We employ top experts, recognized across Canada, who share their skills to shape the next generation of experts.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<div class=\"post__content\">\n<h3>Join the Best<\/h3>\n<p>At Viking Fire Protection, you will find a work environment that fosters your professional development and allows you to become tomorrow\u2019s expert.<\/p>\n<p>For 90 years, our strong reputation has been built on our commitment to providing top-notch fire protection products and services, that perfectly meet our clients\u2019 requirements.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/vikingfire.ca\/job\/\">Apply today<\/a> and join one of the most respected fire protection companies in Canada!<\/p>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>At Viking Fire Protection, we believe in showcasing our dedicated workforce. We are proud to be the employer of choice for the industry\u2019s most experienced and talented fire protection professionals. Because we value our exceptional specialists, across Canada, we dedicate a segment of our blog, the \u201cJoin the Fire Protection Best!\u201d series, to share their [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":9438,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"inline_featured_image":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[43],"tags":[44,47,45,46,48],"class_list":["post-1539","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-employee-stories","tag-dan-clark","tag-fire-alarm","tag-grey-cup","tag-technical-sales-rep","tag-viking-regina","cf"],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/vikingfire.ca\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1539","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/vikingfire.ca\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/vikingfire.ca\/wp-js